1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:10,250 --> 00:00:11,620
I don’t want to film with Po anymore.

3
00:00:12,410 --> 00:00:13,410
I still have feelings for him.

4
00:00:14,720 --> 00:00:16,870
But I don’t want to film with him anymore.

5
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:18,060
I think…

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,000
I have an idea.

7
00:00:20,730 --> 00:00:21,230
But…

8
00:00:21,880 --> 00:00:23,660
When I actually try to draw,

9
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:25,120
I can’t think of anything at all.

10
00:00:26,550 --> 00:00:27,930
I think I have an idea that could help you.

11
00:00:29,260 --> 00:00:30,160
Since…

12
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:31,990
The beginning

13
00:00:32,530 --> 00:00:35,010
Came from your imagination,

14
00:00:35,550 --> 00:00:36,610
Then

15
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:39,650
Let’s recreate that feeling for you.

16
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,450
Khun Sasom.

17
00:02:19,780 --> 00:02:20,840
You.

18
00:02:23,210 --> 00:02:23,770
You don’t have to scold me.

19
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:30,000
I was just startled.

20
00:02:30,730 --> 00:02:33,329
Look, my drawing’s all smudged.

21
00:02:37,230 --> 00:02:38,530
Hey…

22
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:41,790
It’s okay.

23
00:02:42,670 --> 00:02:43,870
I’ll make it up to you.

24
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:45,950
By—

25
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:49,560
Being your model for the rest of my life.

26
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:50,530
Sound good?

27
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:53,590
That won’t be necessary.

28
00:03:01,190 --> 00:03:02,150
Hey, you.

29
00:03:03,730 --> 00:03:05,430
You should stop working now.

30
00:03:06,430 --> 00:03:08,920
This is my time.

31
00:03:09,650 --> 00:03:11,990
Let me finish for a bit longer.

32
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:16,470
Fine.

33
00:03:16,910 --> 00:03:17,800
Then I’m going to bed.

34
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:38,880
Come here.

35
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,150
You.

36
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:08,950
You.

37
00:04:42,530 --> 00:04:43,570
What?

38
00:04:47,330 --> 00:04:48,710
Done yet?

39
00:05:05,820 --> 00:05:07,860
Try this brush.

40
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:08,730
This one.

41
00:05:13,070 --> 00:05:16,610
I’m telling you, the color’s solid.

42
00:05:19,380 --> 00:05:20,540
Po thinks…

43
00:05:21,770 --> 00:05:23,240
This brush is too small.

44
00:05:26,630 --> 00:05:27,950
Then make it bigger.

45
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,090
Hurry up.

46
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,130
Meen.

47
00:11:03,810 --> 00:11:05,280
What do you think we are?

48
00:11:08,590 --> 00:11:09,870
I don’t really know.

49
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:15,370
I don’t usually go for the stoic type.

50
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:18,650
But with you, I don’t know why—

51
00:11:19,490 --> 00:11:20,690
I always go soft.

52
00:11:24,030 --> 00:11:26,100
I don’t really know much about love either.

53
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:29,080
I just know…

54
00:11:30,660 --> 00:11:32,860
I don’t want you to go anywhere.

55
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:38,270
Meen.

56
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:45,590
I want you with me.

57
00:11:51,070 --> 00:11:52,630
What are you talking about?

58
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:56,450
I mean—

59
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:58,920
I’ll be your personal bodyguard.

60
00:11:59,220 --> 00:12:03,010
I’ll protect you, body and heart.

61
00:12:08,150 --> 00:12:10,000
Can you stop dating anyone else?

62
00:12:13,460 --> 00:12:15,250
Let me be the only one who takes care of you.

63
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:59,400
If you really want to keep me to yourself,

64
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:03,040
Then prove it your way.

65
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,240
You.

66
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,410
I actually want more.

67
00:14:23,550 --> 00:14:25,370
But I can’t fit another bite in.

68
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,040
I told you already,

69
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,840
One plate was enough.

70
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:32,770
You…

71
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:36,200
You’re so stubborn.

72
00:14:37,630 --> 00:14:39,660
I’ve told you so many times, and you still won’t listen to me.

73
00:14:41,590 --> 00:14:43,010
That’s because of you.

74
00:14:44,740 --> 00:14:47,720
Why are you suddenly blaming me?

75
00:14:49,550 --> 00:14:50,750
Because your cooking is too good.

76
00:14:52,030 --> 00:14:54,050
How am I supposed to eat less, huh?

77
00:14:56,420 --> 00:14:57,160
Then…

78
00:14:58,890 --> 00:15:01,370
I just won’t cook for you anymore.

79
00:15:05,270 --> 00:15:08,380
I don’t want to be blamed for ruining a national actor’s figure.

80
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:15,000
Here.

81
00:15:16,090 --> 00:15:16,800
I’ll clean up.

82
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,680
It’s okay, I’ll do it.

83
00:15:22,970 --> 00:15:23,470
Mm.

84
00:15:26,890 --> 00:15:27,890
What is it?

85
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,930
I knew you didn’t have anything to wear to P’Ngern’s wedding.

86
00:15:33,220 --> 00:15:34,240
So I had one tailored for you.

87
00:15:54,590 --> 00:15:55,320
Wait.

88
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:56,460
Hold on…

89
00:15:58,290 --> 00:16:00,250
You can just have something like this tailored for someone?

90
00:16:01,880 --> 00:16:02,420
Of course.

91
00:16:04,150 --> 00:16:05,680
If you know their size.

92
00:16:11,310 --> 00:16:12,600
And?

93
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:17,650
How did you know my size?

94
00:16:22,150 --> 00:16:23,740
Why wouldn’t I?

95
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:00,670
Come on.

96
00:17:01,970 --> 00:17:02,700
Let’s go shower.

97
00:17:43,010 --> 00:17:44,370
I told you already,

98
00:17:44,370 --> 00:17:46,440
You don’t have to wait for me every day.

99
00:17:48,030 --> 00:17:50,350
What’s wrong with waiting for my boyfriend?

100
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:54,710
You’re getting shy just saying that.

101
00:17:58,660 --> 00:18:01,340
The shop’s closed, so I came to get you.

102
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:04,940
Come on, I’ll walk you home.

103
00:18:07,850 --> 00:18:11,590
You don’t have to. I can get home on my own.

104
00:18:11,990 --> 00:18:13,320
No.

105
00:18:13,910 --> 00:18:18,810
I promised I’d be your personal bodyguard.

106
00:18:23,290 --> 00:18:24,520
But…

107
00:18:26,150 --> 00:18:27,730
A bodyguard needs to be paid.

108
00:18:31,930 --> 00:18:32,850
Paid with what?

109
00:18:39,750 --> 00:18:42,390
Can I pay with a kiss?

110
00:19:54,290 --> 00:19:55,890
Sure.

111
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,660
Come here.

112
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:06,400
That’s good stuff.

113
00:20:10,350 --> 00:20:11,370
How is it?

114
00:20:11,370 --> 00:20:13,370
Is P’Meen good or not?

115
00:20:13,770 --> 00:20:14,780
Well?

116
00:20:17,350 --> 00:20:18,380
I lost again.

117
00:20:25,650 --> 00:20:27,200
Mr. Bodyguard…

118
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:28,910
You’re terrible at games.

119
00:20:31,330 --> 00:20:32,970
I’m good at protecting.

120
00:20:34,580 --> 00:20:36,400
Not at games.

121
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:40,930
In that case…

122
00:20:42,270 --> 00:20:42,910
Tonight…

123
00:20:44,730 --> 00:20:46,770
Can you protect me properly?

124
00:20:55,660 --> 00:20:57,990
Why wait until tonight? How about now?

125
00:21:02,690 --> 00:21:06,160
You’re insanely cute.

126
00:21:35,950 --> 00:21:36,740
Because a peach

127
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:38,670
Is never just fruit.

128
00:21:42,970 --> 00:21:44,130
It’s care you can hold in your hands.

129
00:21:45,060 --> 00:21:47,370
A gentle promise offered to someone you love.

130
00:21:49,750 --> 00:21:50,500
With a peach,

131
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:52,090
Velvet-skinned and yielding,

132
00:21:52,090 --> 00:21:53,050
Dressed like this,

133
00:21:53,650 --> 00:21:54,150
Sweet with a lingering fragrance,

134
00:21:54,150 --> 00:21:55,160
Who would believe I’m just here carrying bags?

135
00:21:55,450 --> 00:21:56,450
Yet holding a meaning far deeper than it appears.

136
00:21:56,450 --> 00:21:57,570
Then how should I dress?

137
00:21:58,240 --> 00:22:00,400
Come pick your premium peaches

138
00:22:01,230 --> 00:22:01,730
P’Sasom!

139
00:22:01,730 --> 00:22:03,610
Right here at our fresh fruit section!

140
00:22:04,100 --> 00:22:05,560
Oh, sure, sure.

141
00:22:06,050 --> 00:22:06,630
Excuse me.

142
00:22:09,100 --> 00:22:10,000
Let me hold you for a second.

143
00:22:16,420 --> 00:22:18,940
He looks confident in front of a crowd.

144
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:21,230
Just a smile,

145
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:22,960
Just a wave,

146
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:26,180
And everyone screams like they’re spellbound.

147
00:22:31,860 --> 00:22:33,280
But in bed…

148
00:22:33,730 --> 00:22:35,330
I see a different side of him.

149
00:22:36,170 --> 00:22:37,630
Not someone who lives for the fans’ screams,

150
00:22:38,710 --> 00:22:40,830
But someone who prefers my moans.

151
00:22:42,060 --> 00:22:43,880
Not someone performing for fans,

152
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:47,500
But someone who takes control of every inch of my body.

153
00:22:48,930 --> 00:22:50,980
I’m starting to understand that…

154
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:54,140
This is him. Both sides of him.

155
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:58,040
Can I get a heart pose?

156
00:23:01,490 --> 00:23:02,570
Thank you.

157
00:23:35,550 --> 00:23:37,090
How’s P’Kao’s suit?

158
00:23:37,930 --> 00:23:38,780
They’re beautiful.

159
00:23:38,780 --> 00:23:40,350
Easily among the best in Asia.

160
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:44,990
Oh, you’re here, Sasom?

161
00:23:44,990 --> 00:23:45,900
P’Kao, hello.

162
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:46,400
Hello there.

163
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:46,900
Hello.

164
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:48,340
Am I too early, P’Kao?

165
00:23:48,340 --> 00:23:50,000
Not at all. I’ve got your suit ready.

166
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:52,300
I’ll bring it out.

167
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:57,030
Here’s your suit.

168
00:23:58,020 --> 00:24:00,600
Go to Room A, the one at the far left.

169
00:24:02,780 --> 00:24:04,590
I don’t really need to try it on.

170
00:24:04,840 --> 00:24:08,750
Your work is flawless.

171
00:24:09,510 --> 00:24:11,950
You’re too smooth. Just go try it on.

172
00:24:12,380 --> 00:24:12,880
Go on, go on.

173
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:14,270
Why so serious, P’Kao?

174
00:24:14,710 --> 00:24:17,450
Khun Po, I’ll get yours ready first.

175
00:24:22,590 --> 00:24:24,560
Here’s yours, Khun Po.

176
00:24:25,250 --> 00:24:26,420
Thank you.

177
00:24:26,620 --> 00:24:27,570
This way, please.

178
00:24:58,910 --> 00:24:59,410
You.

179
00:24:59,410 --> 00:25:00,000
What?

180
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:00,920
Why did you come in?

181
00:25:02,550 --> 00:25:03,730
No, you—

182
00:25:04,910 --> 00:25:06,250
Someone might see.

183
00:25:06,550 --> 00:25:07,360
No one will.

184
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:08,860
No.

185
00:25:08,860 --> 00:25:10,000
I came in to help you.

186
00:25:10,780 --> 00:25:11,720
You said I could help.

187
00:25:12,020 --> 00:25:14,180
Don’t be stubborn. Go out first.

188
00:25:15,130 --> 00:25:15,930
I’m not leaving.

189
00:25:21,850 --> 00:25:22,450
You—

190
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:25,840
So, baby… what do you need help with today?

191
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:30,480
By the way…

192
00:25:31,170 --> 00:25:34,000
Which piece should I take off for you first?

193
00:25:37,900 --> 00:25:39,250
This one…

194
00:25:42,820 --> 00:25:44,950
Or this one…

195
00:25:47,810 --> 00:25:48,950
Or maybe—

196
00:25:51,570 --> 00:25:52,410
This one.

197
00:25:56,470 --> 00:25:57,060
You—

198
00:25:57,810 --> 00:25:58,420
Don’t.

199
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:00,000
How about this instead—

200
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:03,470
Why don’t I start by taking mine off?

201
00:26:03,720 --> 00:26:04,510
No.

202
00:26:04,810 --> 00:26:05,790
You can’t.

203
00:26:05,990 --> 00:26:07,100
P’Kao might walk in.

204
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:07,900
Just take it off.

205
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:09,340
He’ll— no, no, no—

206
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:10,950
Don’t, you.

207
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:14,230
How is it, Khun Po? Does it fit well?

208
00:26:17,190 --> 00:26:18,190
It fits perfectly.

209
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:21,490
I’ll step out now.

210
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:24,640
I’m here, P’Kao.

211
00:26:25,970 --> 00:26:28,300
Come out already. If you don’t—

212
00:26:31,070 --> 00:26:32,830
P’Kao, I’m coming. Just a second.

213
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:41,980
Ouch—

214
00:26:42,570 --> 00:26:43,210
Sasom!

215
00:26:43,210 --> 00:26:44,470
P’Kao— ouch!

216
00:26:46,870 --> 00:26:48,040
What on earth are you doing?

217
00:26:48,040 --> 00:26:49,490
What were you doing in Khun Po’s fitting room?

218
00:26:50,230 --> 00:26:51,030
P’Kao—

219
00:26:51,770 --> 00:26:52,990
I just went in to check

220
00:26:53,580 --> 00:26:54,810
If the suit fits him.

221
00:26:55,790 --> 00:26:57,470
Check what for?

222
00:26:58,560 --> 00:26:59,510
I didn’t do anything, P’Kao.

223
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:03,300
Who would dare do anything in your fitting room?

224
00:27:03,640 --> 00:27:04,740
I don’t trust you at all.

225
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:08,220
He didn’t do anything to Khun Po, did he?

226
00:27:08,820 --> 00:27:11,710
No, he just helped me try on the suit.

227
00:27:12,360 --> 00:27:14,260
So, does it fit?

228
00:27:15,180 --> 00:27:15,930
It fits perfectly.

229
00:27:16,870 --> 00:27:17,890
It’s very comfortable too.

230
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:20,220
P’Kao’s brand—

231
00:27:21,210 --> 00:27:22,610
Truly lives up to its reputation.

232
00:27:23,540 --> 00:27:24,980
I still have a long way to go.

233
00:27:25,670 --> 00:27:28,220
Aren’t you going to check my suit too, P’Kao?

234
00:27:29,370 --> 00:27:31,640
Just pay and go already.

235
00:27:31,980 --> 00:27:33,820
P’Kao, come on.

236
00:27:34,170 --> 00:27:36,550
Fine, fine. Go on then.

237
00:27:45,350 --> 00:27:46,240
So?

238
00:27:47,380 --> 00:27:50,000
I had this suit made for you. Don’t I deserve a reward?

239
00:27:58,840 --> 00:27:59,740
I can’t deal with you.

240
00:28:00,570 --> 00:28:01,510
What now?

241
00:28:01,510 --> 00:28:02,150
Right here.

242
00:28:34,470 --> 00:28:36,090
Do you really like amusement parks that much?

243
00:28:37,470 --> 00:28:37,970
Yeah.

244
00:28:38,910 --> 00:28:40,130
I love amusement parks.

245
00:28:40,570 --> 00:28:41,970
I just don’t get to go very often.

246
00:28:45,530 --> 00:28:46,540
Because of your dad?

247
00:28:48,810 --> 00:28:49,310
Yeah.

248
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:52,000
He says they’re pointless.

249
00:28:52,350 --> 00:28:53,760
So my mom would take me instead.

250
00:29:01,470 --> 00:29:02,580
It’s okay.

251
00:29:03,570 --> 00:29:04,760
From now on—

252
00:29:05,450 --> 00:29:06,210
Wherever you want to go,

253
00:29:06,700 --> 00:29:08,140
I’ll take you there myself.

254
00:29:14,790 --> 00:29:15,290
Then…

255
00:29:17,460 --> 00:29:20,240
Take me to Disneyland in America.

256
00:29:21,030 --> 00:29:21,730
Sure.

257
00:29:22,620 --> 00:29:23,620
Want to go tomorrow?

258
00:29:24,740 --> 00:29:26,680
I’ve got money to spare lately.

259
00:29:27,320 --> 00:29:28,890
I’ll call Inn and have him book the tickets.

260
00:29:32,780 --> 00:29:33,430
What?

261
00:29:46,630 --> 00:29:48,450
I want to ride the Ferris wheel.

262
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:51,900
But…

263
00:29:52,540 --> 00:29:53,240
But what?

264
00:29:55,470 --> 00:29:55,970
It’s just…

265
00:29:57,050 --> 00:29:58,250
You’re afraid of heights.

266
00:29:59,530 --> 00:30:00,490
Hey, you—

267
00:30:01,230 --> 00:30:01,730
It’s fine.

268
00:30:02,910 --> 00:30:06,050
If it’s enclosed and feels safe like this,

269
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:08,080
I can handle it.

270
00:30:10,950 --> 00:30:11,450
Then…

271
00:30:13,520 --> 00:30:14,520
Want to try it together?

272
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:16,000
If it’s not okay,

273
00:30:16,500 --> 00:30:17,840
We can switch to something else.

274
00:30:21,050 --> 00:30:21,550
Let’s go.

275
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:32,000
If you really had to sit up there,

276
00:30:33,980 --> 00:30:35,220
What do you think you’d be like?

277
00:30:37,050 --> 00:30:39,130
If it’s like this, I’m fine.

278
00:30:40,900 --> 00:30:42,410
But if it had a glass floor,

279
00:30:42,660 --> 00:30:43,950
I’d probably piss myself.

280
00:30:51,420 --> 00:30:53,770
Maybe we should just take pictures instead.

281
00:31:30,900 --> 00:31:32,400
Why are you making that face?

282
00:31:34,970 --> 00:31:36,850
We’re just taking fun photos.

283
00:31:37,540 --> 00:31:38,660
It’s not like we’re posting them for anyone.

284
00:31:39,790 --> 00:31:40,630
Why are you so tense?

285
00:31:43,790 --> 00:31:45,220
If you want something fun,

286
00:31:45,410 --> 00:31:46,910
I’ve got plenty of poses.

287
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,980
Yay!

288
00:31:54,960 --> 00:31:56,000
Hey, jump— quick, jump!

289
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:56,970
One, two, three—

290
00:31:57,560 --> 00:31:58,470
Yay!

291
00:32:08,500 --> 00:32:10,650
So? Is that fun enough for you?

292
00:32:12,180 --> 00:32:13,500
I think it’s pretty fun.

293
00:32:14,190 --> 00:32:15,880
Perfect as a leaked photo of a famous actor.

294
00:32:19,730 --> 00:32:21,140
Can you send it to me?

295
00:32:25,560 --> 00:32:27,400
Unless…

296
00:32:29,320 --> 00:32:30,000
Unless what?

297
00:32:34,300 --> 00:32:36,270
Unless you don’t trust me.

298
00:33:01,510 --> 00:33:02,480
Thank you.

299
00:33:04,530 --> 00:33:05,680
Thank you for what?

300
00:33:09,090 --> 00:33:09,630
Well…

301
00:33:12,410 --> 00:33:14,440
I’ve never taken photos like this with anyone before.

302
00:33:15,330 --> 00:33:15,830
Hey—

303
00:33:16,770 --> 00:33:17,470
Really?

304
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:19,820
So then…

305
00:33:20,870 --> 00:33:22,210
With a boyfriend or something?

306
00:33:28,310 --> 00:33:28,810
Hey.

307
00:33:30,250 --> 00:33:31,680
Are we doing Q&amp;A now?

308
00:33:33,870 --> 00:33:34,370
Yes.

309
00:33:35,660 --> 00:33:37,390
And you have to answer every question.

310
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:40,000
No skipping. Not a single one.

311
00:33:41,040 --> 00:33:41,540
Fine.

312
00:33:42,040 --> 00:33:43,720
But you have to answer too.

313
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:51,990
I’ve never had a boyfriend.

314
00:33:53,280 --> 00:33:54,470
People have hit on me,

315
00:33:55,210 --> 00:33:56,010
And I’ve gone on dates,

316
00:33:56,800 --> 00:33:57,500
But they all ended.

317
00:33:58,890 --> 00:34:00,520
They didn’t want anything serious with me.

318
00:34:01,610 --> 00:34:02,610
So we stopped talking.

319
00:34:10,510 --> 00:34:11,350
Your turn.

320
00:34:24,840 --> 00:34:25,980
I want to know…

321
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:31,179
What happened between you and the old Peach?

322
00:34:46,940 --> 00:34:48,389
You have to answer me.

323
00:34:48,389 --> 00:34:49,150
No skipping.

324
00:34:49,150 --> 00:34:50,000
Hey, you—

325
00:34:50,820 --> 00:34:51,520
Answer me.

326
00:34:53,199 --> 00:34:54,400
I’ll answer you—

327
00:34:54,690 --> 00:34:55,739
After

328
00:34:56,580 --> 00:34:58,010
We ride the Ferris wheel.

329
00:35:07,900 --> 00:35:08,490
Fine.

330
00:35:11,160 --> 00:35:11,660
Let’s go.

331
00:35:12,020 --> 00:35:13,050
Come on.

332
00:35:14,190 --> 00:35:15,330
I’m ready.

333
00:35:22,940 --> 00:35:24,300
I’m leaving this place.

334
00:35:24,940 --> 00:35:25,850
Where are you going, Ton?

335
00:35:27,580 --> 00:35:28,670
Anywhere.

336
00:35:30,550 --> 00:35:32,680
I don’t need your help anymore, Lek.

337
00:35:35,450 --> 00:35:36,810
Remember this.

338
00:35:38,690 --> 00:35:40,350
You ruined my life.

339
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:42,890
You destroyed everything.

340
00:35:45,950 --> 00:35:47,600
You made me feel dead while I was still alive.

341
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:24,370
He simply didn’t want that life anymore.

342
00:36:29,260 --> 00:36:29,760
Actually,

343
00:36:30,980 --> 00:36:33,020
The idea for Peach Lover

344
00:36:33,270 --> 00:36:34,250
Was entirely his.

345
00:36:36,810 --> 00:36:37,610
He knew

346
00:36:38,250 --> 00:36:40,680
What my sexual preferences were.

347
00:36:42,410 --> 00:36:43,610
So he asked me

348
00:36:44,750 --> 00:36:46,970
To film clips for the website together.

349
00:36:52,750 --> 00:36:53,650
And he

350
00:36:53,650 --> 00:36:55,080
Was willing to show his face,

351
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:02,010
While I stayed hidden behind the camera.

352
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:06,440
At first, I wasn’t sure.

353
00:37:08,610 --> 00:37:10,410
No matter how much I liked it,

354
00:37:12,140 --> 00:37:13,230
In the end…

355
00:37:14,470 --> 00:37:16,450
He would be the one who got hurt.

356
00:37:21,630 --> 00:37:22,130
Until he

357
00:37:23,570 --> 00:37:24,810
Insisted he was okay.

358
00:37:26,680 --> 00:37:28,070
That he truly meant it,

359
00:37:28,810 --> 00:37:29,800
That he wanted to do it.

360
00:37:37,070 --> 00:37:39,050
So I let myself follow his lead,

361
00:37:42,210 --> 00:37:42,710
Without

362
00:37:45,330 --> 00:37:46,170
Thinking about anything else.

363
00:37:53,930 --> 00:37:55,270
But the strange thing was,

364
00:37:58,970 --> 00:38:00,710
He never once said he wasn’t okay.

365
00:38:04,120 --> 00:38:06,330
Even when his face in those clips

366
00:38:06,870 --> 00:38:08,220
Spread everywhere,

367
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:12,830
He still chose to keep going.

368
00:38:30,910 --> 00:38:32,190
Until one day,

369
00:38:33,220 --> 00:38:34,120
He came to me

370
00:38:36,880 --> 00:38:39,260
With those images that had gone everywhere

371
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,040
And threw them in my face.

372
00:38:48,120 --> 00:38:50,000
And blamed me, saying…

373
00:38:53,710 --> 00:38:56,810
I was the one who had ruined his life all along.

374
00:39:02,990 --> 00:39:04,800
I didn’t know what to do.

375
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:08,460
I was confused.

376
00:39:12,010 --> 00:39:12,510
It felt like

377
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:18,760
The person I thought was in this with me

378
00:39:22,170 --> 00:39:23,750
The one who had insisted

379
00:39:25,230 --> 00:39:27,180
That this was the life he chose

380
00:39:27,970 --> 00:39:29,210
And was happy to live it—

381
00:39:35,340 --> 00:39:36,880
But those words

382
00:39:42,710 --> 00:39:44,350
Weren’t true at all.

383
00:39:55,920 --> 00:39:58,290
I ended up taking all the blame.

384
00:40:08,670 --> 00:40:09,990
And then he left me.

385
00:40:12,060 --> 00:40:13,070
He never contacted me again.

386
00:40:18,530 --> 00:40:19,770
That’s why, isn’t it…

387
00:40:20,610 --> 00:40:22,390
That’s why you kept asking me again and again

388
00:40:23,480 --> 00:40:24,870
If I was really sure.

389
00:40:25,570 --> 00:40:27,140
About filming clips with you.

390
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:29,520
And showing my face to the audience.

391
00:40:34,220 --> 00:40:35,630
But you have to show your face on camera.

392
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:38,040
Are you okay with that?

393
00:40:40,220 --> 00:40:40,920
I am.

394
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:43,590
You’ve thought it through?

395
00:40:45,660 --> 00:40:46,530
I have.

396
00:40:49,100 --> 00:40:50,770
All of this

397
00:40:52,160 --> 00:40:53,600
Came from the old Peach.

398
00:40:54,630 --> 00:40:55,580
The one who once

399
00:40:56,130 --> 00:40:57,700
Made him believe completely

400
00:40:58,810 --> 00:41:00,570
That everything would be fine—

401
00:41:01,510 --> 00:41:02,800
Before, in the end…

402
00:41:03,640 --> 00:41:05,570
The world collapsed on him alone.

403
00:41:19,600 --> 00:41:21,320
Once I make a decision,

404
00:41:23,790 --> 00:41:25,230
I don’t change my mind.

405
00:41:34,720 --> 00:41:37,550
I’ll never blame you the way he did.

406
00:41:40,910 --> 00:41:42,650
If my life falls apart,

407
00:41:45,170 --> 00:41:47,180
It will be because I chose it.

408
00:42:17,220 --> 00:42:19,130
I won’t regret it.

409
00:42:22,190 --> 00:42:23,830
Because I chose you.

410
00:42:26,550 --> 00:42:27,940
You won’t regret it either, right?

411
00:42:35,250 --> 00:42:36,610
I won’t.

412
00:42:43,920 --> 00:42:45,790
We won’t.

413
00:42:47,420 --> 00:42:48,810
We won’t.

414
00:42:57,310 --> 00:42:58,260
Don’t let go of my hand.

415
00:43:11,500 --> 00:43:12,640
I promise.

416
00:44:07,410 --> 00:44:08,600
Are you sure, Po?

417
00:44:14,330 --> 00:44:14,930
I am.

418
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:21,550
You might still be unsure.

419
00:44:23,730 --> 00:44:26,430
Maybe you think I only want you in bed.

420
00:44:27,270 --> 00:44:28,950
Or just to film clips with you.

421
00:44:32,410 --> 00:44:33,500
But do you know something?

422
00:44:35,430 --> 00:44:37,610
All this time we’ve been together,

423
00:44:41,360 --> 00:44:43,100
I’ve felt really good.

424
00:45:40,000 --> 00:45:41,070
Should we head back to the room?

425
00:45:46,800 --> 00:45:47,860
Hold me.

426
00:45:48,700 --> 00:45:50,350
I don’t have the strength to walk anymore.

427
00:45:58,100 --> 00:45:59,200
Of course.

428
00:46:00,830 --> 00:46:02,060
Let’s get back to the room.

429
00:46:03,500 --> 00:46:04,690
It’s cold out here,

430
00:46:07,010 --> 00:46:07,810
There are mosquitoes.

431
00:46:09,690 --> 00:46:10,890
They’ll leave marks on your skin.

432
00:47:51,920 --> 00:47:52,670
You.

433
00:47:57,320 --> 00:47:58,240
What is it?

434
00:48:02,140 --> 00:48:06,540
I told you how I feel by the pool.

435
00:48:08,870 --> 00:48:10,580
Can I ask you something now?

436
00:48:15,810 --> 00:48:16,860
Right now…

437
00:48:19,080 --> 00:48:21,090
How do you feel about me?

438
00:48:31,660 --> 00:48:33,180
I think…

439
00:48:34,620 --> 00:48:36,280
The fact that I stay with you,

440
00:48:38,670 --> 00:48:40,000
And everything I’ve done,

441
00:48:40,910 --> 00:48:41,860
Up until now,

442
00:48:44,240 --> 00:48:45,820
Should already be my answer.

443
00:48:51,110 --> 00:48:51,960
I do.

444
00:48:55,410 --> 00:48:57,350
I feel so much for you.

445
00:49:00,760 --> 00:49:02,440
So much that I don’t want to be anywhere else.

446
00:49:09,360 --> 00:49:10,920
Thank you.

447
00:50:03,150 --> 00:50:03,980
Good night.

448
00:50:06,010 --> 00:50:07,880
Good night.

449
00:50:42,870 --> 00:50:43,810
Hi, Lek.

450
00:50:45,390 --> 00:50:46,210
Ton.

451
00:51:31,420 --> 00:51:33,310
Today I finally understand

452
00:51:35,530 --> 00:51:37,950
Why he kept asking me over and over

453
00:51:40,000 --> 00:51:41,770
If I was sure.

454
00:51:46,870 --> 00:51:49,280
It wasn’t because he was afraid I’d get hurt.

455
00:51:52,100 --> 00:51:54,260
He was just afraid of getting hurt himself.

456
00:51:55,000 --> 00:51:57,260
Like last time.

457
00:52:07,340 --> 00:52:09,600
Hearing that makes my heart tremble.

458
00:52:11,880 --> 00:52:14,150
It’s clear that…

459
00:52:14,390 --> 00:52:16,100
He hasn’t healed from his old wound.

460
00:52:21,730 --> 00:52:23,260
Even so,

461
00:52:24,010 --> 00:52:25,690
I’ve already made my choice.

462
00:52:35,120 --> 00:52:38,440
I won’t blame him the way that person once blamed me.

463
00:52:40,220 --> 00:52:41,750
Because if my life falls apart,

464
00:52:43,290 --> 00:52:45,320
It will be because I chose it myself.

465
00:52:57,520 --> 00:53:00,390
No matter what lies ahead of me,

466
00:53:01,480 --> 00:53:03,860
I’ll choose to stand right here,

467
00:53:04,450 --> 00:53:05,860
Beside him.

468
00:53:50,240 --> 00:53:51,430
Hi, Lek.

469
00:53:51,430 --> 00:53:52,210
Ton.

470
00:53:52,960 --> 00:53:53,760
What is it?

471
00:53:54,010 --> 00:53:55,890
Why are you staring at me like you’ve seen a ghost?

472
00:53:56,100 --> 00:53:57,030
Is something wrong?

473
00:53:57,330 --> 00:53:58,220
I want to know—

474
00:53:58,220 --> 00:53:59,060
Between you and my friend,

475
00:53:59,750 --> 00:54:01,580
What’s going on with the clips?

476
00:54:01,830 --> 00:54:04,060
I’m not going to let you misunderstand me again.

477
00:54:05,100 --> 00:54:06,830
I don’t want to film clips with you anymore.

478
00:54:07,970 --> 00:54:09,900
Can I ask why?

479
00:54:11,580 --> 00:54:14,150
Because I like you too much.
